Package <Unnamed>

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Heuristic
    A strategy to be utilised by AStarSearch to optimize the search.
    MapGraph<E>
    A Graph to store a Map-like representation containing cities [City] as nodes and roads [Path] as edges.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AStarSearch<E>
    Uses an A* search algorithm, and a heuristic process to find the shortest trip through City objects that will cover all Paths in a List desiredTrips.
    City<E>
    Representation of a node in a MapGraph.
    CustomHeuristic
    A customised Heuristic to find an approximation as to how far away a State is from a goal State.
    EuroMap<E>
    An implementation of the MapGraph Graph representation.
    Path<E>
    Representation of an edge in a MapGraph, connecting two City objects together.
    State<E>
    Stores the current City that AStarSearch is up to, as well as information about the search space such as total cost of the paths taken to this State and the remaining trips to be found by AStarSearch.
    StateComparator<E>
    Compares two States together by their fCost.
    TripPlanner
    Parses input from a file, creates a MapGraph based off of this input, and starts an A* search process to find the cheapest path of planned trips from this input.
    ZeroHeuristic
    A Heuristic that returns 0 for it's approximation, hence essentially simulating Dijksta's algorithm.
